
            HTML (Hypertext markup language)

    Hypertext-> Text with linking to other web pages

    markup is a tag based syntax to build the structure of the page.

    HTML is a case in-sensitive language. It is recommended to use small case.


    Tag Syntax:
    <tag-name>  -> opening tag 
    </tag-name> -> closing tag


    <tag-name attribute-name="value" attribute-name2="value">
        content
    </tag-name>

    <h2>Heading</h2>
    <H2>Heading</H2>

    The latest version of HTML is HTML 5, HTML-5 was introduced in year 2014.
    HTML is used to create structure of the web page.

    HTML tags are nested withing each other.

    <tag1>
        <tag2>
            <tag4></tag4>
        </tag2>
        <tag3></tag3>
    </tag1>
    
    the file extention for html document is .html  / .htm
    
    This is a special Tag, used to depict the document is HTML 5 document
    <!DOCTYPE html>

    <html></html> -> This tag is used to wrap all the content and metadata of the page.


    Element types:

    1) Inline Elements -> these are the elements which takes the only space required to be rendered. and will not add any 
        extra spaces above and below the content.
    2) Block Elements -> these are the elements which takes complete width of the viewport, even if
        the content of the element does not require whole width.
        - it adds extra spaces above and below it.


        There are 4 global attributes: these can be used in any tag of the body.

            - title
            - style
            - class
            - id